Gathering the information (aka Data Wrangling)

Original scraper:

get_nps_func <- function(){
  #Initial code for retrieving data from site
  nps_get <- read_html('https://developer.nps.gov/api/v1/alerts?api_key=...obfuscated...')
  
  #Pulling the JSON data from the html(?)
  nps_json <- nps_get %>% html_text %>% fromJSON
  
  #Pulling the data frame from the JSON data(?)
  nps_data <- nps_json$data
  
  return(nps_data)
}

#Establish connection to local
con_local <- dbConnect(RPostgres::Postgres(),
                       dbname = 'railway',
                       host = Sys.getenv('PGHOST'),
                       port = Sys.getenv('PGPORT'),
                       user = Sys.getenv('PGUSER'),
                       password = Sys.getenv('PGPASSWORD'))

#Create table within local database
dbExecute(con_local, "CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS nps_alerts(
                      id TEXT, url TEXT,
                      title TEXT, parkCode TEXT,
                      description TEXT, category TEXT,
                      lastIndexedDate TEXT, time TIMESTAMPTZ,
                      PRIMARY KEY (id))")

#looping and sleeping
while (TRUE) {
  #Run function to gather data
  nps_input <- get_nps_func()
  
  #Insert from R table created from scrape into local database
  dbExecute (con_local, "INSERT INTO nps_alerts
            (id,
             url,
             title,
             parkCode,
             description,
             category,
             lastIndexedDate,
             time)
             VALUES ($1, $2, $3, $4, $5, $6, $7, current_timestamp)
             ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING",
             params = unname(nps_input))
  print("Transaction ended, waiting for next response.")
  Sys.sleep(3600)
}

Database structure concept

Get parks info and export to csv

#Retrieve data from api
nps_parks_get <- read_html('https://developer.nps.gov/api/v1/parks?limit=1000&api_key=...obfuscated...')
nps_parks_json <- nps_parks_get %>% html_text %>% fromJSON
nps_parks_data <- nps_parks_json$data


#Remove data.frame columns from within data.frame
nps_parks_clean <- subset(nps_parks_data, select = -c(activities, topics, 
                          contacts, entranceFees, entrancePasses, fees,
                          operatingHours, addresses, images))

#Export to csv for uploading in SQL to local database
write.csv(nps_parks_clean, "nps_parks.csv", row.names = FALSE)

Get campgrounds info and export to csv

#Retrieve data from api
query<-list(page="2")
nps_campgrounds_get<-GET("https://developer.nps.gov/api/v1/campgrounds?limit=750&api_key=...obfuscated...",query=query)
http_type(nps_campgrounds_get)

nps_campgrounds_Text<-content(nps_campgrounds_get,as="text")
#jsonRespText

nps_campgrounds_Parsed<-content(nps_campgrounds_get,as="parsed") 
#jsonRespParsed

fromJSON(nps_campgrounds_Text)

#Access data element of whole list and ignore other vectors.
nps_campgrounds_mod<-nps_campgrounds_Parsed$data
#modJson

#Convert JSON resulting list into data frame.
nps_campgrounds_data <- as.data.frame(do.call(rbind, nps_campgrounds_mod))

#Remove data.frame columns from within data.frame
nps_campgrounds_clean <- subset(nps_campgrounds_data, 
                                select = -c(passportStampImages, amenities,
                                            contacts, fees, operatingHours, 
                                            addresses, images, campsites, 
                                            accessibility, multimedia, 
                                            audioDescription, 
                                            isPassportStampLocation,
                                            passportStampLocationDescription))

#Convert to character matrix
nps_campgrounds_clean <- apply(nps_campgrounds_clean,2,as.character)

#Export to csv for uploading in SQL to local database
write.csv(nps_campgrounds_clean, "nps_campgrounds.csv", row.names = FALSE)

SQL Connection

SQL code for setting up tables in local database

CREATE SCHEMA final;

--Create and populate table for alerts data
--NOTE: Final dataset pulled from Railway scrape on 12/3/22 at 5:33pm
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS final.nps_alerts;

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS final.nps_alerts(
    id TEXT, url TEXT, title TEXT, parkCode TEXT, description TEXT,
    category TEXT, lastIndexedDate TEXT, time TIMESTAMPTZ,
    PRIMARY KEY (id),
    CONSTRAINT fk_park
        FOREIGN KEY(parkCode)
            REFERENCES final.nps_parks(parkCode));

COPY final.nps_alerts(id, url, title, parkCode, description, category,
    lastIndexedDate, time)
FROM 'C:\Users\jesse\Documents\Schooling\Willamette-MSDS\DATA-503_Fundementals_of_Data_Engineering\Project\nps_alerts.csv'
WITH (FORMAT csv, HEADER);


--Create and populate table for parks data
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS final.nps_parks;

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS final.nps_parks(
    id TEXT, url TEXT, fullName TEXT, parkCode TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL, description TEXT, 
    latitude TEXT, longitude TEXT, latLong TEXT,
    states TEXT, directionsInfo TEXT, directionsUrl TEXT, weatherInfo TEXT,
    name TEXT NOT NULL, designation TEXT,
    PRIMARY KEY (parkCode));

COPY final.nps_parks(id, url, fullName, parkCode, description, latitude, 
    longitude, latLong, states, directionsInfo, directionsUrl, 
    weatherInfo, name, designation)
FROM 'C:\Users\jesse\Documents\Schooling\Willamette-MSDS\DATA-503_Fundementals_of_Data_Engineering\Project\nps_parks.csv'
WITH (FORMAT csv, HEADER);


--Create and populate table for campgrounds data
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS final.nps_campgrounds;

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS final.nps_campgrounds(
    id TEXT, url TEXT, name TEXT, parkCode TEXT NOT NULL, description TEXT, 
    latitude TEXT, longitude TEXT, latLong TEXT, geometryPoiId TEXT, reservationInfo TEXT, 
    reservationUrl TEXT, regulationsurl TEXT, regulationsOverview TEXT, directionsOverview TEXT, 
    directionsUrl TEXT, weatherOverview TEXT, numberOfSitesReservable TEXT,
    numberOfSitesFirstComeFirstServe TEXT, lastIndexedDate TEXT,
    PRIMARY KEY (id),
    CONSTRAINT fk_park
        FOREIGN KEY(parkCode)
            REFERENCES final.nps_parks(parkCode));

COPY final.nps_campgrounds(id, url, name, parkCode, description, latitude, 
    longitude, latLong, geometryPoiId, reservationInfo, reservationUrl,
    regulationsurl, regulationsOverview, directionsOverview, directionsUrl,
    weatherOverview, numberOfSitesReservable, numberOfSitesFirstComeFirstServe,
    lastIndexedDate)
FROM 'C:\Users\jesse\Documents\Schooling\Willamette-MSDS\DATA-503_Fundementals_of_Data_Engineering\Project\nps_campgrounds.csv'
WITH (FORMAT csv, HEADER);

--Cleanup on campgrounds
ALTER TABLE final.nps_campgrounds
DROP COLUMN lastIndexedDate;

SQL connection to local database to read tables in to R

#Establish connection to local
con <- dbConnect(RPostgres::Postgres(),
                       dbname = 'data503_analysis',
                       host = Sys.getenv('PGHOST'),
                       port = Sys.getenv('PGPORT'),
                       user = Sys.getenv('PGUSER'),
                       password = Sys.getenv('PGPASSWORD'),
                       options="-c search_path=final")

alerts <- dbReadTable(con, "nps_alerts")
parks <- dbReadTable(con, "nps_parks")
campgrounds <- dbReadTable(con, "nps_campgrounds")

Exploratory Analysis

Using R to analyze data

Plotting frequency of alerts

alerts %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(category, category, function(x)-length(x))))+
    geom_bar(fill='#2D4B1E', color='#2D4B1E')+
    labs(title="National Parks Service Alert Notifications", x="Alert type", y="Frequency")+
    labs(subtitle="Between 11/2/22 and 12/3/22")+
    theme_minimal()+
    theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = '#FEF8F2', color = FALSE))+
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face='bold'))+
    theme(axis.title = element_text(face="italic"))+
    theme(axis.text = element_text(size=12, face="bold"))

More Data Wrangling

Filtering alerts for Park Closures only

closures <- alerts %>% filter(category == "Park Closure")
closures <- subset(closures, select = -c(id, category, time))
closures <- mutate(closures, reason="")

Creating reason list based on descriptions

Note: This was done manually using Excel due to time constraints
write.csv(closures, "closures_reason.csv")

closures_edited <- read.csv("closures_reason_edited.csv")

Adding coordinates into new dataset

closures_lat_long <- merge(x=closures_edited,

Mapping

leaflet(closures_lat_long) %>% 
  addTiles() %>%
  addCircleMarkers(~as.numeric(longitude), ~as.numeric(latitude),
                    popup=paste(closures_lat_long$fullname,"<br>", "Closure comment: ",
                    closures_lat_long$description), weight=5, radius = 5)

Adding color to dataset for marker designation on final map

unique(closures_lat_long$reason)
## [1] "Miscellaneous"        "Seasonal"             "Staffing"            
## [4] "Outages/Construction" "Weather"              "Event"               
## [7] "Fire"                 "Unsafe Conditions"    "Covid"
colorPalette <- c("#999999", "#E69F00", "#56B4E9", "#009E73", "#F0E442",
                  "#0072B2", "#D55E00", "#CC79A7", "#000000")

closures_lat_long <- closures_lat_long %>% 
  mutate(color = case_when(reason == "Miscellaneous" ~ "#999999", 
                           reason == "Seasonal" ~ "#009E73", 
                           reason == "Staffing" ~ "#0072B2",
                           reason == "Outages/Construction" ~ "#F0E442",
                           reason == "Weather" ~ "#56B4E9",
                           reason == "Event" ~ "#E69F00",
                           reason == "Fire" ~ "#CC79A7",
                           reason == "Unsafe Conditions" ~ "#D55E00",
                           reason == "Covid" ~ "#000000"))

Final map plot

leaflet(closures_lat_long) %>% 
  addTiles() %>%
  #addProviderTiles(providers$Esri.NatGeoWorldMap) %>% 
  addCircleMarkers(~as.numeric(longitude), ~as.numeric(latitude),
                    popup=paste(closures_lat_long$fullname,"<br>", "Closure comment: ",
                    closures_lat_long$description), weight=5, radius = 5,
                    color = closures_lat_long$color) %>% 
  setView(lng = -96.5670822, lat = 38.44023613, zoom = 4)
